Text:
I was able to fix it myself, but it doesn't took correct
I had Docker on my host and there is Docker in Minikube
Docker in Minukube had issues
I had to minikube ssh into minikube VM and follow this post 

[http://stackoverflow.com/questions/23111631/cannot-download-docker-images-behind-a-proxy][1]
and it all works nows,

There should be a better way of doing this, on starting minikube i have passed docker env looks like that did not work


  [1]: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/23111631/cannot-download-docker-images-behind-a-proxy

Docker in Minukube had issues
I had to minikube ssh into minikube VM and follow this post 

[http://stackoverflow.com/questions/23111631/cannot-download-docker-images-behind-a-proxy][1]
and it all works nows,

There should be a better way of doing this, on starting minikube i have passed docker env looks like that did not work

Initially i did this, which did not work

     
    minikube start --docker-env HTTP_PROXY=http://xxxx:8080 --docker-env HTTPS_PROXY=http://xxxx:8080 
    --docker-env NO_PROXY=localhost,127.0.0.0/8,192.0.0.0/8 --extra-config=kubelet.PodInfraContainerImage=myhub/pause:3.0
     
I had set the same env variable inside Minikube VM, to make it work

  [1]: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/23111631/cannot-download-docker-images-behind-a-proxy
